BBC: Titanic Southampton Remembers
2012-04-17 06:05:30 GMT
Titanic, Southampton Remembers tells untold stories to mark the 100th Anniversary of the sinking of the RMS Titanic.To mark the 100th Anniversary of the sinking of the RMS Titanic in April 2012, the BBC will broadcast a special range of programmes on TV, radio and online, exploring the people, history craftsmanship and legends surrounding the events of that fateful night.As part of the special programmes to be broadcast, Titanic, Southampton Remembers on BBC One (South) tells the untold stories of the fateful night that resulted in a huge loss of lives.
